EBOLA HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - SUDAN (WESTERN
EQUATORIA) (04)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Tue 8 Jun 2004
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organisation (WHO), CSR, Disease
Outbreak News,
Mon 7 Jun 2004 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_06_07/en/>

Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever in South Sudan - WHO Update 4
---------------------------------------------------
As of Sun 6 June 2004, the health authorities of Yambio County
have reported a total of 28 cases, including 7 deaths from Ebola
haemorrhagic fever, (case fatality, 25 percent), in Yambio, Western
Equatoria, south Sudan (see previous report
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_06_01a/en/>
or ProMED-mail post (03) below).
Active surveillance and follow-up of contacts has been reinforced;
overall, 124 contacts are currently being followed up. Isolation
wards are fully operational with trained nursing staff. Additional
equipment for personal protection, collecting samples, shipment of
samples and communications has been received. A special team
has been organized and trained for social mobilization. Key
messages concerning the disease, its modes of transmission and
necessary prevention measures have been distributed widely in the
community.
For more information about Ebola haemorrhagic fever, please see
the WHO fact sheet
<http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs103/en/>
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[These figures represent an increase of 3 cases and one death
since the previous WHO report from Yambio on Mon 31 May
2004, suggesting that the outbreak is being contained
successfully. - Mod.CP]
